scatter levels

scatter2 = function(i, X, Y){
  df = data %>% mutate(y = X, x = im_share) %>% select(Pref, x, y, pop, year) %>% filter(year == i)
  p = ggplot(df, aes(x = x, y = y, label = Pref)) + theme_bw()+
    geom_point() + geom_hline(yintercept = 0, color = 'lightgrey') + 
    geom_vline(xintercept = 0, , color = 'lightgrey') +
    geom_text_repel() +
    geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE, color = "gray") + #,mapping = aes(weight = pop)
    scale_x_continuous(expand=c(0,0), limits = c(0,2.5)) +
    scale_y_continuous(expand=c(0,0)) +
    labs(title = paste(Y, 'in', i),
         x = "Population share of foreign residents",
         y = Y) +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) +
    theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
          panel.grid.minor = element_blank())
  return(p)
}
a = '(a) Per capita public assistance expenditure'
b = '(b) Per capita public assistance expenditure'
c = '(c) Population share of public assistance recipients'
d = '(d) Population share of public assistance recipients'
plot_list = list(scatter2(2010, data$welfare, a), scatter2(2010, data$welfare_share, c),
                 scatter2(2021, data$welfare, b), scatter2(2022, data$welfare_share, d))
grid.arrange(grobs = plot_list, ncol = 2)

Scatter change

data$logwelfare = log(data$welfare)
scatter = function(start, end, X, Y, Title, xlab, ylab){
  df = data %>% mutate(y = Y, x = X) %>% select(Pref, x, y, pop, year)
  old = subset(df, year == start)
  new = subset(df, year == end)
  sc = merge(new, old, by = 'Pref')
  p = ggplot(sc, aes(x = x.x - x.y, y = y.x - y.y, label = Pref)) + theme_bw()+
    geom_point() + geom_hline(yintercept = 0, color = 'lightgrey') + 
    geom_vline(xintercept = 0, color = 'lightgrey') +
    geom_text_repel() +
    geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE, color = "gray") +#,mapping = aes(weight = pop.x)
    labs(title = Title,
         x = xlab, y = ylab) +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) +
    theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
          panel.grid.minor = element_blank())
  return(p)
}
a = scatter(start = 2010, end= 2021, X = data$im_share, Y= data$logwelfare,
            Title = '(a) Eligible foreign residents and per capita expenditure',
            xlab = "Change in share of eligible foreign residents: 2010-2021",
            ylab = 'Change in log per capita expenditure: 2010-2021')
b = scatter(start = 2010, end= 2022, X = data$im_share, Y= data$welfare_share,
            Title = '(b) Eligible foreign residents and population share of recipients',
            xlab = "Change in share of eligible foreign residents: 2010-2022",
            ylab = 'Change in share on public assistance: 2010-2022')
c = scatter(start = 2010, end= 2021, X = data$im_share2, Y= data$logwelfare,
            Title = '(c) Non-eligible foreign residents and per capita expenditure',
            xlab = "Change in share of non-eligible foreign residents: 2010-2021",
            ylab = 'Change in log per capita expenditure: 2010-2021')
d = scatter(start = 2010, end= 2022, X = data$im_share2, Y= data$welfare_share,
            Title = '(d) Non-eligible foreign residents and population share of recipients',
            xlab = "Change in share of non-eligible foreign residents: 2010-2022",
            ylab = 'Change in share on public assistance: 2010-2022')
grid.arrange(grobs = list(a, b, c, d), ncol = 2)

National trend

japan = data %>% select(year, pop, welfare_pop, welfare_pref, welfare_city, im, total)
japan = japan %>% group_by(year) %>% summarise(across(where(is.numeric), ~ sum(., na.rm = TRUE))) %>% ungroup()
japan = japan %>% mutate(im_share = 100*im/pop, all_im_share = 100*total/pop, im_share2 = 100*(total-im)/pop,
                         welfare = 1000*(welfare_pref + welfare_city)/pop,
                         welfare_share = 100*welfare_pop/pop)
# labels only 2010, 2015, 2020, 2022
all_im_label = sprintf('%.2f',round(japan$all_im_share, 2))
im_label = sprintf('%.2f',round(japan$im_share, 2))
im_label2 = sprintf('%.2f',round(japan$im_share2, 2))
wel_label = sprintf('%.2f',round(japan$welfare_share, 2))
ggplot(data = japan, aes(x = year)) +
  theme_classic() +
  geom_line(aes(y = im_share, color = 'Eligible foreign population share'), size = 1.5) +
  geom_line(aes(y = im_share2, color = 'Non-eligible foreign population share'), size = 1.5) +
  geom_line(aes(y = welfare_share, color = 'Population share of people on public assistance'), 
            size = 1.5, linetype = 'dotted') +
  geom_text(aes(label = im_label, y = im_share), vjust = -1) +
  geom_text(aes(label = im_label2, y = im_share2), vjust = 1.5) +
  geom_text(aes(label = wel_label, y = welfare_share), vjust = -1.0) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c(#'Foreign population share (all)' = "grey", 
                                'Eligible foreign population share' = "black", 
                                'Non-eligible foreign population share' = "darkgrey", 
                                'Population share of people on public assistance'= "black")) +
  scale_x_continuous(name ='', breaks = seq(2010, 2022, 1)) +
  scale_y_continuous(name = "Population share", limits=c(0, 2), expand=c(0,0),) +
  theme(legend.position='bottom', legend.title = element_blank(), legend.key.size = unit(2, "cm"),
        plot.margin = unit(c(2, 2, 0, 2), "mm"),
        legend.box.spacing = unit(0, "mm")) +
  guides(colour = guide_legend(nrow = 1))

Maps

df1 = data %>% filter(year == 2022 & fips !=0) %>% 
  select(pref, fips, im_share, im_share2, welfare_share) %>% arrange(fips)
df2 = data %>% filter(year == 2021 & fips !=0) %>% 
  select(welfare, fips) %>% arrange(fips)
data = df1 %>% left_join(df2, by = 'fips')
vars = c('welfare_share', 'im_share', 'im_share2')
data[, vars] = lapply(data[, vars], function(x) round(x, 2))
im1 = data %>% select(fips, im_share) %>% arrange(fips)
im2 = data %>% select(fips, im_share2) %>% arrange(fips)
myMap = function(n, df, Title) {
  colnames(df)[2] = 'im'
  im = df
  (breaks = (seq(from = 0.18, to = 2.4, length.out = 1 + n)))
  (breaks = round(breaks, 2))
  (breaks = as.character(breaks))
  (Im = sort(unique(im$im)))
  (Im_cut = cut(Im, breaks = breaks, include.lowest = T, labels = F))
  (color_palette = colorRampPalette(c("white", "black"))(n))  
  (fill = color_palette[Im_cut])
  (color_mapping = tibble(im = Im, fill))
  map_data = im %>% 
    left_join(color_mapping, by = "im"); head(map_data)
  JapanPrefMap(col = map_data$fill, border = 'black', axes = F, inset = T) # inset for Okinawa
  (legend_labels <- paste0(head(breaks, -1), "-", tail(breaks, -1)))
  legend(x = 142, y = 38, legend = legend_labels, fill = color_palette, bty = 'n',
         border = "white", title = paste("Share of eligible foreign residents in 2022"),  cex = 1) 
}
myMap(9, im1, "Share of eligible foreign residents in 2022")

myMap(9, im2, "Share of non-eligible foreign residents in 2022")

wel1 = data %>% select(fips, welfare) %>% arrange(fips)
wel2 = data %>% select(fips, welfare_share) %>% arrange(fips)
myMap = function(n, df, Title, Min, Max) {
  colnames(df)[2] = 'im'
  im = df
  (breaks = (seq(from = Min, to = Max, length.out = 1 + n)))
  (breaks = round(breaks, 2))
  (breaks = as.character(breaks))
  (Im = sort(unique(im$im)))
  (Im_cut = cut(Im, breaks = breaks, include.lowest = T, labels = F))
  (color_palette = colorRampPalette(c("white", "black"))(n))  
  (fill = color_palette[Im_cut])
  (color_mapping = tibble(im = Im, fill))
  map_data = im %>% 
    left_join(color_mapping, by = "im"); head(map_data)
  JapanPrefMap(col = map_data$fill, border = 'black', axes = F, inset = T) # inset for Okinawa
  (legend_labels <- paste0(head(breaks, -1), "-", tail(breaks, -1)))
  legend(x = 142, y = 38, legend = legend_labels, fill = color_palette, bty = 'n',
         border = "white", title = Title,  cex = 1) 

}
myMap(9, wel1, 'Per capital expenditure in 2021', 7800, 62000)
